Steps performed:

Download the zipped data
Unzip the data
Read relevant data files, including "Y_test.txt", "Y_train.txt", "X_test.txt", "X_train.txt", "subject_test.txt" and "subject_train.txt"
Merges the training and the test sets to create one data set using cbind
Extracts only the measurements on the mean and standard deviation for each measurement using grep
Uses descriptive activity names to name the activities in the data set
Appropriately labels the data set with descriptive variable names with gsub
Creates a second, independent tidy data set with the average of each variable for each activity and each subject

